			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDoN and Calming problems<a name="44970"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 8 04 12:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sneak is your friend.
<br />

<br />
*edit*
<br />

<br />
I guess I should elaborate.  Being a puller it is key to understand mob LoS/sneak radius.  Basically a mob only has Line of Sight view 180 degrees from it's front.  So figure an invisible straight line from the tip of their nose running parallel to it's back (at times it seems less than 180 degrees, but that's probably just server/client play or something).  You can easily sneak up to a mob on the wall in any ldon, large mobs are especially easy.  It's always a safe bet to sneak up to a doorway when you open a door just for the chance that the mob is facing away from you.
<br />

<br />
I have used sneak to pull/drag/look around in everything from Ldon to Ikkinz+ GoD raids.  It's also a good escape tool to have next to your fade for the chance that a see invis mob turns as soon as you fade.  In GoD this is especially loving since mobs move at stupid speeds and trash mobs hit for 2k.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
