				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDoN and Calming problems<a name="45251"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 10 04 12:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't like to sneak. because I forget to turn it off, and end up running from my pull at REALLY slow speed!
<br />

<br />
I use the 3rd person camera view to check inside the doorways.  Any time I am pulling, I have the first to the free range 3rd person campera views set all the way out, all the way down, level to me and looking centered on me.  Then I can open the door at longest range, swing the camera around and see everrythign that is just next to the doorway. Lull, then step up and work on the room!
<br />

<br />
I have the direct camera buttons hotkeyed around my Number pad, so I can switch cameras instantly, at need.  Great not only for pulling but for CC work, knowing about adds, and just knowing what everyone in your party is up to and where they are at!
<br />

<br />
Just my thoughts.
<br />

<br />
Tenosh on Prexus.</span></td>
