Lulling in Hard LDoNs has been and always WILL be the least predictable. It was engineered this way to provide a MUCH bigger challenge to break through the dungeon. Lull song was NOT nerfed to resist more, just not last as long. I'm still pretty new to pulling hard LDoNs and the first time was pretty rough even though I'd prepared myself by reading up as much as I could on here(had charisma at 280 only tried to lull blue cons when possible). 
